quest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":33,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Pratyman was born about 1349, in Bacton, Suffolk, England, his father, John Pratyman, was 28 and his mother, Mrs. John Pratyman, was 27. He married Agnes Hobart in 1375, in Bacton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1407, in his hometown, at the age of 59, and was buried in Bacton, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"about 1349–1407":"umbes 1349–1407","1349–1407":"1349–1407","1354–1410":"1354–1410","1376–1420":"1376–1420","1378–1440":"1378–1440","1322–Male":"1322–Surnud","1324–Female":"1324–Surnud","1440":"1440","1382":"1382","before 1349":"enne 1349","1349":"1349","1324":"1324","about 1349":"umbes 1349","1378":"1378","Abt 1376":"umbes 1376","1322":"1322","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1376":"1376","1354":"1354","1375":"1375","1407":"1407","Bacton, Suffolk, England":"Bacton, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1349–1407":"noin 1349–1407","1349–1407":"1349–1407","1354–1410":"1354–1410","1376–1420":"1376–1420","1378–1440":"1378–1440","1322–Male":"1322–Kuollut","1324–Female":"1324–Kuollut","1440":"1440","1382":"1382","before 1349":"ennen vuotta 1349","1349":"1349","1324":"1324","about 1349":"noin 1349","1378":"1378","Abt 1376":"noin 1376","1322":"1322","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1376":